The paper discusses algorithms for decision making tasks in probabilistic graphical models, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence and machine learning (cs.AI). The focus on optimization and efficiency suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The use of algorithms for selecting observations and reducing uncertainty suggests a connection to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The consideration of multiple sensors and energy conservation in buildings suggests a connection to control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the use of information theory and the complexity analysis of decision theoretic value of information objective functions suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT).
